org.jorlib.frameworks.columnGeneration.master

Class MasterData<T,U extends AbstractColumn<T,V>,V extends AbstractPricingProblem<T>,X>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jorlib.frameworks.columnGeneration.master.MasterData<T,U,V,X>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of model data
    U - type of column
    V - type of pricing problem
    X - type of variable, e.g. an IloNumVar in cplex

    public class MasterData<T,U extends AbstractColumn<T,V>,V extends AbstractPricingProblem<T>,X>
extends Object
    This is a data object which is being managed by the Master problem. The same data object is passed to the cutHandlers. Therefore, the object can be used to pass information from the master problem to the classes which separate valid inequalities (and also in the opposite direction).
    Version:
    13-4-2015
    Author:
    Joris Kinable
